<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE rdf:RDF [
	<!ENTITY bfo "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/">
	<!ENTITY dc "http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">
	<!ENTITY dcterms "http://purl.org/dc/terms/">
	<!ENTITY dtype "http://www.linkedmodel.org/schema/dtype#">
	<!ENTITY iof-av "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/annotation/">
	<!ENTITY iof-construct "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/">
	<!ENTITY iof-core "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/">
	<!ENTITY iof-ind "https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/individual/">
	<!ENTITY owl "http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#">
	<!ENTITY rdf "http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#">
	<!ENTITY rdfs "http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#">
	<!ENTITY skos "http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#">
	<!ENTITY xsd "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#">
]>
<rdf:RDF xml:base="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/utility/PrescribedAllenIntervalAlgebraUtility/"
	xmlns:bfo="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/"
	xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"
	xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/"
	xmlns:dtype="http://www.linkedmodel.org/schema/dtype#"
	xmlns:iof-av="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/annotation/"
	xmlns:iof-construct="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/"
	xmlns:iof-core="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/"
	xmlns:iof-ind="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/individual/"
	xmlns:owl="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#"
	xmlns:rdf="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#"
	xmlns:rdfs="http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#"
	xmlns:skos="http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#"
	xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#">
	
	<owl:Ontology rdf:about="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/utility/PrescribedAllenIntervalAlgebraUtility/">
		<rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">Prescribed Allen Interval Algebra Utility Property Ontology</rdfs:label>
		<dcterms:abstract>This utility module provides object properties for representing prescriptive temporal relations between plan specifications using patterns inspired by Allen interval algebra. The relations are intended to capture how the planned processes prescribed by two plan specifications are required to stand in temporal relation for conformity to the structural constraints of a plan. These properties do not describe actual temporal relations in execution traces, but rather the intended temporal configuration prescribed by the plan.</dcterms:abstract>
		<dcterms:contributor>Ana Nikolov, OAGi</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Boonserm Kulvatunyou, NIST</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Gabriela Henning, NIST</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:contributor>Milos Drobnjakovic, OAGi</dcterms:contributor>
		<dcterms:license rdf:datatype="&xsd;anyURI">http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT</dcterms:license>
		<owl:imports rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/Core/"/>
		<owl:versionIRI rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/202601/core/utility/PrescribedAllenIntervalAlgebraUtility/"/>
		<iof-av:copyright>Copyright (c) 2022, 2023, 2024, 2025, 2026 Open Applications Group</iof-av:copyright>
		<iof-av:maturity rdf:resource="&iof-ind;Released"/>
	</owl:Ontology>
	

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="&iof-construct;prescribedToMeet">
	<rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="&iof-construct;isAbout"/>
	<rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">prescribed to meet</rdfs:label>
	<rdfs:domain rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/utility/PrescribedAllenIntervalAlgebraUtility/"/>
	<rdfs:range rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<skos:example>The equilibration operation is prescribed to meet the loading operation; The hold step is prescribed to meet the transfer step</skos:example>
	<iof-av:explanatoryNote>This relation captures a prescriptive temporal ordering between two plan specifications. It is used to represent that, according to the structural constraints of a plan, one planned process is to meet another. This does not assert that the two processes actually meet in an execution trace, but rather defines the intended temporal adjacency required for conformity to the plan specification.</iof-av:explanatoryNote>
	<iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">relation between two plan specifications indicating that the planned process prescribed by the first must meet the planned process prescribed by the second in order to conform to the ordering constraints of the plan specification</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="&iof-construct;prescribedToTemporallyFinish">
	<rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="&iof-construct;isAbout"/>
	<rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">prescribed to temporally finish</rdfs:label>
	<rdfs:domain rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/utility/PrescribedAllenIntervalAlgebraUtility/"/>
	<rdfs:range rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<skos:example>The buffer addition operation is prescribed to temporally finish the agitation operation; The final rinse step is prescribed to temporally finish the cleaning operation</skos:example>
	<iof-av:explanatoryNote>This relation captures a prescriptive temporal ordering between two plan specifications. It is used to represent that, according to the structural constraints of a plan, the planned process prescribed by the first is to temporally finish the planned process prescribed by the second. This does not assert that the two processes actually stand in this relation in an execution trace, but rather defines the intended temporal configuration required for conformity to the plan specification.</iof-av:explanatoryNote>
	<iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">relation between two plan specifications indicating that the planned process prescribed by the first must temporally finish the planned process prescribed by the second in order to conform to the ordering constraints of the plan specification</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="&iof-construct;prescribedToTemporallyOverlap">
	<rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="&iof-construct;isAbout"/>
	<rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">prescribed to temporally overlap</rdfs:label>
	<rdfs:domain rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/utility/PrescribedAllenIntervalAlgebraUtility/"/>
	<rdfs:range rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<skos:example>The pH monitoring operation is prescribed to temporally overlap the titration operation; The temperature recording step is prescribed to temporally overlap the incubation step</skos:example>
	<iof-av:explanatoryNote>This relation captures a prescriptive temporal ordering between two plan specifications. It is used to represent that, according to the structural constraints of a plan, the planned process prescribed by the first is to temporally overlap the planned process prescribed by the second. This does not assert that the two processes actually stand in this relation in an execution trace, but rather defines the intended temporal configuration required for conformity to the plan specification.</iof-av:explanatoryNote>
	<iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">relation between two plan specifications indicating that the planned process prescribed by the first must temporally overlap the planned process prescribed by the second in order to conform to the ordering constraints of the plan specification</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="&iof-construct;prescribedToTemporallyStart">
	<rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="&iof-construct;isAbout"/>
	<rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">prescribed to temporally start</rdfs:label>
	<rdfs:domain rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/utility/PrescribedAllenIntervalAlgebraUtility/"/>
	<rdfs:range rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<skos:example>The media feed operation is prescribed to temporally start the cultivation operation; The timer initiation step is prescribed to temporally start the mixing step</skos:example>
	<iof-av:explanatoryNote>This relation captures a prescriptive temporal ordering between two plan specifications. It is used to represent that, according to the structural constraints of a plan, the planned process prescribed by the first is to temporally start the planned process prescribed by the second. This does not assert that the two processes actually stand in this relation in an execution trace, but rather defines the intended temporal configuration required for conformity to the plan specification.</iof-av:explanatoryNote>
	<iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">relation between two plan specifications indicating that the planned process prescribed by the first must temporally start the planned process prescribed by the second in order to conform to the ordering constraints of the plan specification</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="&iof-construct;prescribedToOccurSimultaneouslyWith">
	<rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="&iof-construct;isAbout"/>
	<rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">prescribed to occur simultaneously with</rdfs:label>
	<rdfs:domain rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/utility/PrescribedAllenIntervalAlgebraUtility/"/>
	<rdfs:range rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<skos:example>The conductivity monitoring step is prescribed to occur simultaneously with the elution operation; The pressure recording step is prescribed to occur simultaneously with the filtration operation</skos:example>
	<iof-av:explanatoryNote>This relation captures a prescriptive temporal ordering between two plan specifications. It is used to represent that, according to the structural constraints of a plan, the planned processes prescribed by the two plan specifications are to occur simultaneously. This does not assert that the two processes actually occur simultaneously in an execution trace, but rather defines the intended temporal coincidence required for conformity to the plan specification.</iof-av:explanatoryNote>
	<iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">relation between two plan specifications indicating that the planned processes prescribed by the two plan specifications must occur simultaneously in order to conform to the ordering constraints of the plan specification</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="&iof-construct;prescribedToOccurDuring">
	<rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="&iof-construct;isAbout"/>
	<rdfs:label xml:lang="en-US">prescribed to occur during</rdfs:label>
	<rdfs:domain rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/utility/PrescribedAllenIntervalAlgebraUtility/"/>
	<rdfs:range rdf:resource="&iof-construct;PlanSpecification"/>
	<skos:example>The sampling operation is prescribed to occur during the fermentation operation; The visual inspection step is prescribed to occur during the transfer operation</skos:example>
	<iof-av:explanatoryNote>This relation captures a prescriptive temporal ordering between two plan specifications. It is used to represent that, according to the structural constraints of a plan, the planned process prescribed by the first is to occur during the planned process prescribed by the second. This does not assert that the two processes actually stand in this relation in an execution trace, but rather defines the intended temporal configuration required for conformity to the plan specification.</iof-av:explanatoryNote>
	<iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en-US">relation between two plan specifications indicating that the planned process prescribed by the first must occur during the planned process prescribed by the second in order to conform to the ordering constraints of the plan specification</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
</owl:ObjectProperty>

</rdf:RDF>
